We used to go a nine hour shift. Threepence an hour. Threepence and hour. Oh shocking it was. Anyway it was a job. Oh I was - oh - twelve or eighteen months I suppose on that job. And - it was the time of - Queen {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}Victoria{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}'s funeral. Well this particular night we had - to get the royal train ready and it was up on the embankment in the op
en air and it poured of rain all - nearly all night and we had - we had to get this - get this royal train ready for the Queen's funeral. Pleurisy and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12456976\charrsid15100875 
pneumonia}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 . Oh dear, I was bad too. They thought I was going to die at that time. And - I had to leave tha
