Yes. Sevenpence an hour. Fifty hours a week, twenty-nine and tuppence. Well that lasted for - oh - three or four months I suppose, nice job that was. See, what did I do after that? I got a job at Watney's brewery, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Pimlico Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, they wanted labourers there. That was a nice little job there, when we got there six o'clock in the morning, got to be at Victoria, 
Watneys brewery, it's still there, and - there was a gallon of black beer and a gallon of ale on the canteen table, we could help ourselves. Got this job at Watneys Brewery. And - we always used to carry a bit of rubber tubing about with us - of a daytime
.
 Knock the old bung out of a barrel, have a drink whenever we wanted it. And we were allowed one quart of beer to come home of a night time. And there was this gallon on the table at dinner times aw well, and we were always allowed a quart - to come home 
