ith of a night time. Well we used to take our tea in a - a can there, with a cork in it you know. Well one day they got a - one of the chaps there had found out where there was a - what they called a pipe, that was - ooh, a long barrel - about forty-eight
 
gallons I think, port wine. We didn't - we didn't want to take our quart of beer home that night so we - we siphoned it out, poured it into our beer can, I come home with a - a - with a quart of port wine - plus what I'd had during the daytime. Cor dear o
h dear.
