 the middle of the road they'd put a chalk mark, you see, and we had to skate this - and if you got it - if you got the flattened milk tin on the line - then - you had to run backwards and the one that was on the other side'd run after you and he'd have t
o
 carry you back, piggy back, back to your base again. That was - that was - that was one of the things we used to do. And another thing we used to do, in - the roads were nearly all Macadmaised in those days - all lumps of granite like that you see and ro
lled down. Well we used to dig one or two pieces out and make a hole and stick one - one piece on the edge of - on the lip of the hole and we'd have another bit and - and try knock it off with another one you see. Oh - the games we used to get up to.

