Were we allowed to get dirty? You couldn't help it at times according to what game we were playing. I know sometimes when we came in y
ou know, ready to go to bed of a night, the state you're - go on, out there and wash. We had to go and wash in the sink then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 But they didn't bother too much tough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh no. Oh as long you were reasonably clean you see, hands and face.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Your parents didn't discourage you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh no. Oh no, they didn't - very very seldom they'd bar us from playing with somebody else you know, very very seldom that happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What sort of reasons would they have if they did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well, perhaps they might have been dirtier kids than we were you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Liable to have fleas and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 That's right, it could have been that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you belong to any y
outh organisations apart from the chapel and things like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh no. No, when I started work - they had a - what they called an institute there, and they'd got a library with about couple of thousand books I suppose and - they had their swimming clubs and their -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 This is Price's is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Price's, yes. They had their swimming club and their - cricket and football clubs and that you know and I was a - I was a famous swimmer out of that lot, oh yes. I really was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you have any hobbies while you were at school, did you keep any pets?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
No, I went to - I went to a woodwork centre you know once a week. Be taught carpentry. And - and quite a bit of knowledge - and I was interested in woodwork at the time you see, I was greatly interested in that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 While you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you collect anything at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
No. Cigarette cards, oh yes. Cigarette cards. Oh yes. Oh yes, they were in vogue, you got cigarette cards with everything nearly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you ever go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
No. That never entered - only for tiddlers that's all. In a pond, or up the Wandle. Oh yes, I used to go tiddler fishing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you go with a load of the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Yes, couple or three of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How about cycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No cycling - couldn't afford a bike, oh dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 They were still a luxury were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
I'll say they were. The only cycles that we used to get, we used to have a - hire a bike out for - fourpence an hour I think they'd lend us a bike, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 That was quite a lot of money wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh yes. Then I remember once I got this bike out - and me and another chap - we cycled down to Reigate, and - I don't think free wheels were invented by that time }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10492923\charrsid15100875 but}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  this time I'm speaking of - and riding down Reigate Hill, pu
t me feet up on the fork, top of the forks there - going along there hell for leather, and the blooming brake didn't work. The chain broke and I had to - to guide it right into a hedge, and trust it - how I got out of it. Anyway a chappie come along and h
e give me a bit of copper wire which I - I mended the chain and we rode back with that. And I -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Was this after you were working at Price's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
I expect so, yes, because I - I'd got the tanner or shilling an hour for the bike you see, tanner an hour for the bike or fourpence an hour I believe it were, I forget now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Did you ever go to theatres or cinemas or anything while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
No, sometimes the teacher of a Saturday would take us to one of the museums or Tower; of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}, something like that you know, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}
Westminster{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} Abbey. The teacher was - he was a jolly nice teacher. A Mr Hutchins, most kind he was. And of a Friday afternoon he'd buy perhaps a pound of mixed fruit drops, he'd put 'em on a slat and he'd come round the clas
s and we'd all take one each, a mixed fruit drop. There were about forty in class so you can pretty well guess he must have bought about a pound of them. And if anybody had come there with very shabby boots or perhaps no boots at all, he'd go and buy 'em 
a pair of boots. Yes. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Do you think he had money of his own or did he do this out of his salary?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10492923\charrsid15100875 wouldn\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
 know how he got the money or whether he could afford it or not but - he'd go and buy the kid a pair of boots and perhaps when the 
kid got 'em home his mother'd go and pawn them. Oh yes, that was - that was a quite a common thing to do. Oh - no more boots for you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Were there many children barefoot in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh yes. Behind out of their trousers, oh a very poor neig
hbourhood Battersea was at that time, very very poor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Were you ever given lessons by one of your parents or anyone else before you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 I should think about four or five. 
Then - our school money was then threeha'ence a week. We had to pay for that - pay for our schooling. Threeha'pence a week. And there was a little tin but I remember in Plough Road Battersea. They made it into a public baths now, slipper baths. And we use
d to go there and we used to - we used to have to pay this threeha'pence a week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 That was quite an expense for your family then with several children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh yes, it was. Well - education was not compulsory in those days you know. Oh no, I don't they think were. But when they opened another school, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Winstanley Road{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} school in Battersea, that is, I think is when education became compulsory. And they was free then you see, we didn't have to pay anymore school money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Do you remember how old you were when you stopped paying school money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
I suppose I went to this small school at threeha'pence a - threeha'pence a week for about couple of years, I must have been about six or seven then I suppose. I know I was in the infants }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10492923\charrsid15100875 class}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 , I do know that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
When you first started school what time in the morning did you go and come back, what were the hours of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Nine o'clock 'til twelve. Twelve 'til two was - dinner time. And two 'til four or half past.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 You started off going for a full day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh yes, that's right. It was nine 'til twelve, two hour break, and then two and a half hours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What sort of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
A board - just an ordinary board school you know, elementary. A board school, yes. What - what was known - school board for {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 was the dominating people of those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How many schools did you go to all told?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
I went to this one when I left the - threeha'pence a week school, then I went to Latchmere school and I - was in Latchmere school right the way
 through. Started - I started at Latchmere school in what they knew - known as the junior mixed, that was boys and girls you know and - weren't old enough for the adult classes and too old for the - youngster class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Do you remember what age this would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Eight or nine I suppose, yes. I suppose eight, about eight, because I'll tell you why. When you started at school - you were in the - first off second standard, according to what - how far advanced you were in your education, you see, you got a 
test and if you were a bit above the normal you were put in standard two, well every year we used to have an examination and if you passed you went up one standard higher. Well I left I was in what was known as the ex seventh standard. I'd gone through th
e second, third, fourth, fifth, sixth and seventh. And - when I got out of the seventh standard I put what - was called then the ex-seventh, well then you're more or less the teachers }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10492923\charrsid15100875 lackey}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 , that - that's about what - they'd taught you as much as they coul
d really. Gone through all the forms, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Do you remember any of the teachers very plainly at the infants school or anything about the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
No, nothing much, you see I was only about four or five years of age, I can't remember much about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 At the Latchmere school how did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well just }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10492923\charrsid15100875 walked it}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
, I wasn't very far away you see. Only about - couple or three hundred yards I suppose. Oh yes, it wasn't - was no traveling you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 So you used to go on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh yes, quite, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Where did you have your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Well if we - if we didn't go home we - got a dinner ticket you see or we used to pay the ha'penny and go to this place on Lavender Hill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 So part of the time you'd have it at school and part of the time at home?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 You liked your school very much and you liked at least one of your teachers?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
I did like my school, there's no mistake about it, I did, I loved my school. I was looking forward to the tim
e to go - well as I told you, I ran away from the old man you know when he got a job for me. I wanted to go to school, I didn't want to go to work. Not that I was afraid of work but I - I loved my school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How did you feel about the teachers in general?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh all right, I used to get on very nice with the teachers.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Was there any of them you particularly disliked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No, I don't think there was, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No, only in - impre
ssed on us - the - necessity of being truthful and honest. And clean you know, the - they ordinary amenities of life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
How about manners or way of speaking, did they try and make you speak in any particular way or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 If mother and father was sp
eaking, if we butted in we got a smack you know - a holly good - speak when you're spoken to. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
How about if you did something the teachers disapproved of, what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well you either got one, two or - four cuts across the hand with
 a cane. Or perhaps you'd have to bend over a chair and get it on your backside with a cane, my God he used to put it on too. And if you - anything very - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10492923\charrsid15100875 
flagrant}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  - you'd have to go down to the headmaster's study and your name would go in what they called
 the punishment book. You'd got to do something very drastic to get that. And he - he'd put down perhaps four or six of the very best, my God, and he did - he did - he did pay us. He - I only went down there once.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Were the girls punished the same as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
No, I don't think so, no. They only stood up in a corner - with their hands on their heads, something like that - that was the - the girls punishment, what I can remember of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Were you ever given any other punishments except the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How about lines and things like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh yes, oh we used to get our lines all right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How about detention, did they used to keep you in late?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Yes, if - if you were naughty the teacher'd stop in perhaps half an hour.
 And - you'd have to - you'd have to - write out lines while you was - being kept in after school hours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What sort of offences would you be punished for?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Well, if you misbehaved yourself in class well now - one lark we used to get up to you kno
w - pen nibs, if you pressed the points down like that you see you got a kind of a fork bit like that. Well we used to get - blotting paper, make balls of it and go like that you know, and flick 'em perhaps to get some - specially if there was any ink on 
it, dip the blotting paper in the ink you know and - if you were lucky and got a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10492923\charrsid15100875 bulls eye}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 , bang like that. That was the sort of thing you did cop out for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 You'd get the cane for that would you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How about for bad work or blots on your book?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh well - I was a very dirty writer in my younger days, and the teacher - dubbed me inky Scott, that was my name and - if I got blots on my copy books or any of me exercise book he'd blue pencil mark it - mark Inky's trademark. Oh they were a
ll my - my - my copybooks were all - they were murder.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 You didn't used to get the came for something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Did they give you punishments at all for anything like that or just tell you off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh just a telling off you know, d
idn't get punished for it. But anyway, I - he broke me of it as you see, my handwriting now I've -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
No, not at all. If we got any homework to do, perhaps father, if you know - what's your home
work like tonight Harry? Oh so and so father. Let's have a look at it. Well that's - yes, that's not too bad but you've done something here, you know, you've spelt that word wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did he ever visit the school at all or meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Only o
n prize giving day, mother used to come, of course father didn't 'cos he was at work. Prize giving.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Your mother would come up on prize giving day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 On prize giving day, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did she ever meet the teachers any other time or go up to the schoo
l on any other occasions?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
No I don't think so. In our summer holiday we used to go what we - what we called scrumping at that day, that was robbing orchards or - pinching fruit off growing trees. Well we discovered a place, about a six or seven foot
 wall, the other side of which they'd got peaches growing along, on the south wall you see. Well one of my mates lifted - lifted me up, I'm hanging over the wall you know, getting peaches and handing 'em down, all of a sudden I toppled over. About eight f
oot - gardener come running out there - oh he give me a clump at the side of the head, he said, come on. I - I was like this you know, I thought he was gong to have me }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10492923\charrsid15100875 locked up}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  or something, which I've no doubt he could have done. He took, me to his green 
- house and I think he'd got about - a couple or three hundred flower pots. He said, you sit down there he said, I want you to red - red ochre all those flower pots, he says, and don't you try and get away because I've got me eye on you. And he's going ou
t - a blooming great big tin of red ochre with a paintbrush and - oh dear - when I'd done I was like a red Indian. Anyway, he gave me a shilling and he gave me a dinner. But when I got home }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10492923\charrsid15100875 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 ou know - red ochre all down - oh - ooh, up to bed you. After I'd 
cleaned myself up, oh - and that was up - nearly to Wimbledon Common We had to walk - walk up there and walk back, well we didn't take any notice of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Was it more common in those days for people - to punish children themselves, I don't think a gardener today would do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh yes, well nothing like that. Serve you right, that's what I got from me father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
At this school you were at did the other children come from similar types of home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Yes, all - all about that type.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did the t
eachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
No, only - I was about the exception I think as I told you, this teacher took a great interest in me and I used to go to his house after tea of a night time and he'd - he'd giv
e me lessons you know, give me problems to work out and - algebra, and euclyd, I've forgotten every word about them now. Same as me decimal fractions you see, I'd forgotten every word about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Were there any gangs in the school at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No, only our own playground - kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
No, if they were deformed or anything - or weakly you know we - we didn't go in for gymnastics, they were not allowed to go in for gymnastics. They'd only got a vaulting horse and a pair of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10492923\charrsid15100875 parallel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
 bars that's all. And one horizontal bar, that's about all we'd got you know for our gymnastic exercises.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 This is the only sort of thing where children would be left out of things?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after her house or family?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No, no. Only she - only if she was having babies, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What would happen when your mother was ill or confined to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well
 we got a midwife coming in, that's about all. Perhaps one of the neighbours would come in during the daytime and - and - get a bit of food for us kiddies or mother. One of the neighbours would - the little circle we were living - you know, our neighbours
, they were all - they were friends and neighbours, no mistake about it
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 They were more or less one and the same thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 That's right, yes, we'd all help one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Yes. Mother's broth
er. Mother's - two brothers. One lived at Chelsea and one lived the other end of Battersea - Battersea Bridge - Bridge Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How much did they see of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh now and again they'd call in you know and father's - father's nephews over - they were all in the billiard line as well. They used to come now and again to see us you know. Perhaps on a Sundays, come to tea and stay the evening }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10492923\charrsid15100875 you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Would they always see them in the home or would they meet them somewhere else on occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No, see them in the homes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Where did your parents see their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Where?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did they come in the home at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh yes. Now and again you know. Come in and see how the old chap was going on. Perhaps his workmates you know, people he'd worked with. Or perhaps his nephews, his own nephews would come along, which were our cousins of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did your mother have any friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh yes, she had one or two particular friends, she used to go and visit in the afternoon sometimes you know, she'd have an - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10492923\charrsid15100875 hour}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  to spare, but - go along and see them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Would these be friends of your father as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No. No mostly female friends of mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 And your father would have his own friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Have his own circle of friends you know, wherever they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
When friends were invited into the home would they be offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh yes. Perhaps mother would invite 'em to Sunday tea or something like this you see, well then we'd get a bit of a spread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How often would this be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well not too often you can bet your life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Were these on particular days or occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
No, perhaps they'd go out and meet them - well, doing anything Sunday? Well come round and have a cup of tea, kind of thing you know, just like that, of the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Would you any that the friends invited in were your mother's friends or your father' friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Mother's friends mostly. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
You say friends would call in casually without invitation, when would this be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh sometime during the day, if - if they or mother had got the time to - spare you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did your parents go out visiting friends and neighbours very much?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No, not - not a lot. No. They occasionally did but very very seldom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 You say you
r cousins and relatives used to come to you, did you used to go to their place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 I used to, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How about your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No, I can't say that we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
People often tell us that in those days people made their own amusements, what did your parents do when they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10492923\charrsid15100875 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 ot together with their friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh we either had musical evening or sit - sit - and chat, one or two of my father's nephews, they used to play cards. That's right, or - either cards or musical. Then if they'd - 
if they were male well the old man's friends or relatives, they'd go down the pub perhaps and - fetch back a couple of bottle of beer and perhaps we'd have a - finish up with a musical evening with a - with a drink.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 So you might start off with a game of cards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Yes, or - all right let's come out and have a drink. We never had any - any - intoxicants in the house, never. Only at Christmas time. And father used to belong to a slate club, you know what they called slate clubs, generally in a pub and 
out of their share out - the members used to have to have a bottle of spirits, and whisky was three and six a bottle. Three and six. Out of their share out they had to spend that with the publican you see. Or else five cigars which was about a - one and t
hreepence, one and sixpence. My - that's right, oh yes. Looking after the money and we - we went to his premises you see for the club meeting
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Do you remember much of the pub life of Battersea in those days before the war, when you were a child, people often tell us that the pubs were very lively in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh yes. Well they'd open at five o'clock in the morning, they'd shut up at twelve or half past of a night time. That was the public hours - licensing hourse in those days. Five in the mornin
g - and you could get a - a rum and coffee for threeha'pence. That was a little tot of rum and a cup of coffee for threeha'pence and - you could get a - a nip of whisky for tuppence and a - the women used to - what they call a half a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10492923\charrsid15100875 quarter}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  and two out, w
ell this half a quarter, I don't know whether it was a gill or half a gill or what it was but - used to get a little }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10492923\charrsid15100875 miniature}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  pewter shaped measure and used to give you two small wine glasses and there used to be a drink each - this little wine glass full
 of this gin and that was the - the women met one another went and had a drink that was invariably what it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did women go into pubs very often in those days?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh yes, some - some of the old girls, they were proper old }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10492923\charrsid15100875 boozers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 , you believe me.
 Oh some of the old girls they'd - in there directly they were - directly they were out, free - free of a morning, you know, he kids were at school, come up the pub. And you' see 'em, they'd sit there perhaps for about an hour. Yes. Some of 'em would. Don
't ever remember my mother doing it, well she hadn't got the money for it for one thing. And she wasn't a drinker in a - in another way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Could they take their children in with them then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh yes. Oh yes. Now when my father used to take me out Sund
ay mornings - mother's say, how many heart cakes have you had? We used to get a - ha'penny heart cake, what they called - a kind of a little bun effort you know - father'd have his half a pint of beer which was a penny, just the four ale, and a heart cake
 for me or perhaps a - a small - what they called apony glass of lemonade or gingerbeer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 And used to be able to go in the bar with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Many people divide society into different social classes, in that time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one class and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh well, there was a - was a difference in classes. If you were poor you were - you remained poor. But if you were a little above that well - then - they were a class by themselves - stuck up sort of a - effort they were you know, as a rule.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Could you tell me what the different classes were, how many different classes would you say there were in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
It's rather a funny question, I can't say - you were either very poor or you were comfortably off, it was - that was the angle. Just that little disparity between the two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Which class would you say you belonged to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well the poorer class. Oh yes, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What sort of people belonged to the same class as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well all our neighbours you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Where would you draw the line, would you include shop assistants and people like this or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How about -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 If you got an office job you were a little bit above the o
rdinary work - working people. Kind of a white collar you know, if you got a white collar you'd got a better job. They were the up - they were the up and coming people, that's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort d
ifferently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No, we just took things as they came.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Were you ever taught to touch you cap or show respect in some way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Yes, to doctors and clergymen. My mother used to say, now if you meet Doctor so and so, or you meet
 a clergyman, if you say good morning to 'em just doff your cap. Yes. And if - if you were out with one of 'em - father or mother - and you failed to do that - oh you got - you - what did I tell you before you came out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Was there anyone you called sir
 or madam or master? Any special term like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Only the doctor - doctor or clergymen, we'd give 'em a sir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Not out of the way, no. No I shouldn't say so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 In your district who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 In what category do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
In your opinion who were considered the most important people in those days in your district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Most important people? Only doctors and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10492923\charrsid15100875 clergymen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 , that's a
bout all I think. And if a shopkeeper, it was his own shop kind of thing you know. If he had his own business. That's so, yes, that's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you come into contact with these sort of people very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No, only when we - went to their shops for errands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Why were these people considered important to you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Well they were a step above the labouring class if you can understand that, you know they didn't go out to work and work with their hands kind of thing. They were just the one little step above the ordinary workmen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 It's more a less a division between the manual worker and the ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 That's - that's so. Yes, that's so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What sort of people would you say went to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Wouldn't know because we didn't do much churching ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How about chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
We only went on a Sunday afternoon to our Sunday school. That was the only time we went to church. Our Band of Hope. That's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the 
same standard of living or would you say there were different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No, I should say they were all practically the same standard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Were some families though of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh some of them were - yes, some of 'em - 
families were very very rough. Now - you see the parents had no - control over their kids kind of thing, and they simply ran wild. Mother'd say, don't you go and play with so and so, you know, that's the only time we were barred from - choosing our compan
ions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Was this a difference in the amount of money going }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10492923\charrsid15100875 into}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  the home or why do you think some did go rough as it were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Well some - I think they mostly went rough you know and - the parents used to drink perhaps. They'd go in a pub every night. 
Well the old - as I say, the - the father's - beer was only tuppence a pint and mother would have what - a glass of porter or a - what they called porter, which was a black beer was - about threepence a quarter. Father's beer was fourpence quart. Now with
 a couple or three coppers they could sit there all night with a - with a drink.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 You think a family would get rough if they started spending too much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Yes, spending too much on drink. And of course they let their kids run wild, they'd got no time
 for their kids. And some of them were atrocious little devils. I'll tell you one little incident that stuck out in my mind. Opposite where we lived they had a general shop, grocers and that you know, and one little perisher, he crawled in there, opened t
h
e door, crawled in there, they used to have flat counters you know, and he'd - he'd crawl underneath there and empty the blooming till and come away. Well - Stroud was the shopkeepers name - complained the police. Police come down you know and he rounded 
u
p about a dozen of us kids, we'd got to go on - up to the police station - an identity - identity parade. Well - somebody said that they saw the kid coming out from the shop and - told the shopkeeper about it and we all had to go up to the police station 
in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Battersea High Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} - In Battersea Bridge Road rather - put on an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 identity}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  parade. This - this party who - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 who\rquote d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
 made the report out about us - picked me out. Cor - I dirtied me britch - oh - I was scared out of me life. And I - I'd - I - I was innocen
t of course. What they were going to do to me I had - got no idea, I was only about so high you know and only about seven or eight years of age. Anyway th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 
is kid, this - Barlow his name }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 was - always remember he'd got two different coloured eyes, he'd got a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 br}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
own eye and a blue eye, yes. Oh he was a perisher. To the school teacher - to the schoolteachers and all. He'd think nothing - our slates used to be in a rack at the top of the desk you know, you know and sling a - sling one of the slates - slates at the
 school teacher. Oh he was a devil.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Were there many of these sort of children in a class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh quite a - quite a number of 'em - different - scattered about you know. We knew they were little perishers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you see many policemen around Battersea as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Policemen? Yes. Always - always policemen patrolling somewhere or other.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What did you think of the police as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh if - if we saw one we'd run. Yes, get out of his way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How do you think the police treated people in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
The police? All right as long as you behaved your self, but if you - if you - if you went off - off the rails a bit you - you copped out. Oh yes. You'd either get a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 demeaned}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  good clumping from the copper, or else he'd take his strap 
off and give you a belting with that. Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 He didn't take you along to the police station?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Very seldom. - Used to take the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 law}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  into his own hands, administer the punishment that he thought.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 This was pretty customary in those days was it with the police?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh - oh yes. And in some of the turnings in Battersea they didn't walk about single they walked about in twos. In some of the slum districts of Battersea. Yes. Wasn't safe for one all by himself, they'd have him. Be in an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 upstairs}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 window}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 , drop a brick on his head or something like that. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Did you ever go into these rough districts yourself as a boy or did you steer clear of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Not unless we were - not unless we were bound to go in there or - just for idle curios
ity you know but - we steered clear of those dangerous corners and streets. Oh we had one or two streets in Battersea here - terrible, fights all day long. There were - in one - one street there - there was two Irish people - Irish - lived next door to on
e another, that was the D}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
mmas and the Kellys. They used to go out Saturday night and they'd fight like murder, you know, after a few drinks they'd come out and have a damned good scrap in the middle of the road. And - the women would call, dirty }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 old}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  so and
 so's. What's dirty? Up come their clothes and they show all their clean underclothing. Oh - oh dear, that was nothing. The Kellys and Dummas are at it again, come on, let's come and have a look. And they'd got - they'd got a loose railing, well whichever
 one was out there first out come this loose iron railing you know and the one who got that they're generally the victors. Oh funny that was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you see much of this sort of thing in Battersea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh yes, quite a - quite a lot. And then - sometimes
 the - the men in the pub you know, there used to be a little pub in our road, Culvert Road - the Culvert Arms, it was the proper name of it but - the common name was the rat pit and on a Sunday morning - they'd put their rat traps down and one or two'd f
etch their terriers in there you know, they'd let the rats loose in the bar and - let these two terriers, you know, go for the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 rat. Yes. And then - they'd have - bird singing competitions, linnets as a rule you know, little tiny boxes they were, and what they used to do to these linnets was blind them. With red hot }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 needle}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  in their eyes and they'd sin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  like - oh, they'd sing beautifully. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What else was there going on round Battersea in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well they - they used to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 play}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  cards and domi
noes and darts in the pubs you know. For their pints. Then we had a - we had a couple of fairgrounds in Batteresea. A coconut shie down the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}York Road{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Were they there all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 All the time, yes. And we had - we had a - a little circus
 place. Oh yes, they had circus there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Were these permanent or did they come every so often?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No, it was there permanent. Manleys circus, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What sort of things did they have there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh they had - equestrian riding you know, a couple of clowns, a bit }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 of acrobatic}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
 and - perhaps a little sketch they'd put on. Yes. And they'd had - what they called penny gas, they had little side shows you know. Shadow pantomimes and - well - fat ladies and the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 biggest rats}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  you know, a copy that's abo
ut what they were, oh, rat about that size, they were coypus, I know what they are now but we didn't at the time. The bearded ladies you know, tattoed - tattoed ladies, tattoed man. A penny to go in you know and - that was the first time I'd seen - moving
 
pictures. Paid a penny to go in, you - and I can remember that picture even now. I don't suppose I was about seven or eight. And that was a - they would play cards, it was a French picture. There's two blokes playing cards on the side of the kerb, ban cam
e by with the tailboard down. They got up with their cards and playing cards on the - on the tailboard of this van, 'til it went round the corner, that was the finish of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 That was more or less the whole film?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well that was - yes, about five or
 ten minutes I suppose. Then perhaps they'd put a - a short comic one on, drunken sailors or something like that you know. That was - when I went home and told - father and mother I'd seen moving pictures they wouldn't believe me. I said, well you go up a
nd have a look. Up {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Falcon Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, that's where it is, in the - in the swing yard. Oh they got a big fair there going as well. Another one on Lavender hill. Swings and roundabouts there and they were more or less permanent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 This is where you spent some of
 your evenings when you were at school did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Talking about rough and respectable families, do you remember any distinction of this sort between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No, I - I - I wouldn't know about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did your mot
her and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
No, I don't think so, they just took things as they came you know, I don't think they made any distinction at all. Just took people as they found them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Do you think your mothe
r saw herself as belonging to a particular social group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
No. No. Well she hadn't the time you see to - take - any active - amenities outside the hole, she had no time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 I wonder if she thought of herself as being working class or lower class?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No, she - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another? You said you thought it was difficult if you started off poor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
It certainly was, now, I don't think there was much chance of getting out of the rut. I don't think there was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Do you know of anyone who did in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No, can't say that I do. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Yes, there was one fellow lived at - further up the street there - he 
always used to go out Sundays, he - I suppose he used to go to church - with a top hat, always. When the morning, if he went to church in the morning, he'd come home, take his top hat off, he'd put a cap on and go in the pub. He would. His name was Delaco
re, I don't know whether he's French, but that was his name, Delacrois. How it was spelled I don't know, but anyway he was a - and he was a - a proper spoken - gentlemanly spoken fellow, he was a well educated man I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What sort of reasons would you have for describing a man as a real gentleman?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well his speech I suppose and his habits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What did you think of him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh h
e was a grasping sort, I - I remember when - if father was out of work you know, we've got no rent for you today. All right, you must have it next week or out you go. And it would too. Oh yes, if you didn't pay your rent they'd pull all your things out on
 
the - on the pavement, oh yes. Oh no, no chance no, they could let the house to somebody else you know, and get their rent. Oh yes, you couldn't default with your rent. As I say, when the old man was out of work mother used to pawn everything that was paw
n
able. Now I'd got some prizes from school, and I remember the names of the - the two books, they were lovely books, gilt edge you know and lovely bound, one was called Lorna Doone and the other one was Tales from Shakespeare, they were all condensed Shake
spearean plays you know in story form, and father - mum pawned those and I never saw 'em any more. I always remember those two books. Oh I was proud of those. I got - I got certificates from school, I got - I've still got those certificates.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 It must have hurt you when your books were pawned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh yes. Well everything that was pawnable was pawned, you had to do it to keep the kids going you know and - if - if possible pay the rent. We never - we never had that experience, being turned out of our house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 But you had to pawn things to avoid it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 I can show you my school certificates now. Scripture certificates.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 You said you had the Charity Organisation come round, how did they treat you?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well as though you were dirt. You put an appl
ication in either by letter or - personal call at their office and they'd send a representative round to see you. Ask you all questions, how many in family, what did you have to eat, what was your father's job, what did your mother do, didn't your mother 
g
o out to work, why can't she go out to work, how many of you children are going to work? None of us, we were all - school age or younger, not old enough for school. How many in family? So and so. How many chairs have you got? Well you don't want a - you d
on't want a music stool do you? Well - what like that might be over there. You sell that. And come round and see us again. Anything that was - they thought was surplus in the home we'd got to sell. Which you got absolutely nothing for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 in fact}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  ever give you any help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Not that I - not to - not to our people. So I don't think - I don't think - father or mother would apply to them. But I - of course we'd heard what - what they were with other people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 So you didn't actually have them round to your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
You were conscious that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet, what did you think about it at the time, as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh I used to feel very very sorry for 'em. Cor if I had some money I'd give - I'd mother so and so. Oh dear - oh wouldn't I like to go and pick up some money so that I could help mother. Oh dear.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Were you conscious of this as a schoolboy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh yes, I was conscious of it. That was my one prayer, if I could only find some money or get hold
 of some money to help my mother. Yes. I used to feel so very very sorry for poor old mum you know. Perhaps I'd see her sitting there crying you know, well - don't know what her trouble was you know - she - oh go on, it's nothing, I don't feel well, if yo
u
 asked her what she was crying for. Well of course I don't know what - perhaps her and father had had a row, I don't know you see. But she'd be sitting there crying and that used to make me cry too. See poor old mum crying like that. More or less it was t
he - our poverty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
When there was someone in the district whom the people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they showed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Any what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
If the people round about didn't like the way someone was behaving did they have any special way of showing their dislike?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
No, I don't think so. I think the-'d just ignore them you know. Wouldn't speak to 'em or something like that you know. Or forbid their children to play with their - their - other people's kids. They'd want to know why, perhaps the two women'd have a row.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 You have told me about your leisure time with talent competitions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Did you used to take your wife to these, before you were married, were you doing these sort to things then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
No, just parties - when we were invited - when I was invited out to a party she invariably came with me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did your parents always meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No, they didn't interfere with - our own friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 You weren't expected to be home at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh on. No, no. Not as we were getting along, of course when we were children it was different.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How long had you known your wife when you got married,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well since I was sixteen, I'd known her - she was my really first }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 sweetheart}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 , 
she really was, and we were sweethearts right up to the day she died, I will say that about her. We were always together, we didn't want anybody else. We were together that was all right. Until we went to parties of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How old were you when you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Twenty and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How old was your wife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Same age, within a month or two. Well her birthday was in May and mine was in June. They were both in the same year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What sort of things did you used to do while you were courting,
 did you go out walking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Just out walking, oh yes. You see, while we were courting she was at work at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Chelsea{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 and I lived in Battersea. So I used to go over and meet her, generally she used to come out from her laundry job at eight o'clock at night. 
Well perhaps I was home at half past six see or six o'clock, had me tea and washed and changed, just have a walk over to Chelsea and meet her and we'd - stay about for about an hour, an hour and a half, and we'd part, you know I'd see her home, and I'd co
me home and she'd got to her - say at - when she was at home. That's all we did, just walk round and - the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Chelsea{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} squares.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you have a long engagement?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Well I suppose we were about - yes, about a twelve month. I told you, we got engaged when I was about nineteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you save up before getting married or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Did I what? Well - I had - I had matrimony in me mind and whatever I could, if I put a couple or three bob away you know whenever I could I did so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did your parents help you in setting up a home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Could you describe the wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh I can't no. No, we simply walked round the church, came home, we had a bit of a spread, our friends came round you know, we had a musical evening and that was that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 When was the actual ceremony, at what time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
I'm telling you, it was a - on a Christmas morning at half past eight in the morning. And we walked to the church, was only about a quarter of mile I suppose, and walked back again - to home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Were there any other couples getting married too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
There were six couples getting married at the same time, we stood in a row in front of the alter. And the old padre come along you know and - wilt thou - and you know, the usual marriage ceremony, individually. Oh
 yes. Then we filed into the vestry and signed our name you know and - one after the other and then - out - out we came. Had to rush it because of the morning service you see, Christmas morning, about half past ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you have a honeymoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Where did you live after you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Well - within a - couple of hundred yards from where we lived when we were kids. In Culvert Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
You told me you lived in this first one about ten months, how many times did you move between getting married and the end of 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh about four or five - I'd say about five. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How old was your wife when you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Same age as myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did your wife have any other jobs apart from the laundry before she married?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No. No
. If - if - if and when she did go to work it was always laundry work,; nothing else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 And she did this occasionally throughout your married life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
That's right, when I - when I was - when I'd fallen out of work and we'd got no money coming in wel
l she'd turn out, she could always get a job. Always get a job. 'Cos her particular branch in the laundry business was packing and sorting which - they had to be trained up to you see and they were very few - one of the best - what can I say - the most pr
oficient in the laundry business.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did your wife enjoy her work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 I think so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How did you feel about her going out to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well I didn't mind at that, I was glad of it. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 You told me that you had four children between 1
905 and 1920 and you lost the two little boys, were your children born at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you have any medical help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Only the doctor you see, when - when the confinement was due, go and call the doctor in. The midwife would be there befo
rehand, getting all the preparations ready if she was in labour she - you see, the midwife would know what to do and doctor'd come round and see her, oh she'll be all right for another three or four hours, I'll come back later.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you help at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
No. I was out the way. Cleared out of it as soon as ever I could - conveniently get away I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How soon was your wife out of bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How soon? About eight or ten days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Was this for a full day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well she got up in the mornings as a ru
le you see for the first couple odd days and then when she got her - her - sealegs as you might say well then she stayed up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
How did you manage while your wife was in bed, for cooking and looking after yourself and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well I told you the sis
ter lived quite near, well it was either the sister come and - did a bit if cleaning for me or the lady we were living with, the landlady we were living with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you have a nurse at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No. Just the midwife.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 You told me in the courting p
eriod that people were much more moral than they are today?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Could you just tell me something about that again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh the - subject of sex was taboo between me and my wife, what other people did I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 But you think this would be fairly common?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh I think so, yes. Of course now and - occasionally you would hear of a - a chap getting a girl into trouble and they got married and that was that. I think there was less - less of that promiscuity going about that - than ever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you really know what to expect in childbirth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Well of course she'd heard something and - she'd recount it to me and I'd hear something, whether it was right or not we didn't know until the actual time came along. Some of it was all right but some of it was - oh - all piffle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 So really you were that innocent, you didn't really have a true idea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh no. No, no. 'Course after the first child was born then - she'd know all about it then, she'd got all the answers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How much did you have to do with the children when they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 were less}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  than a year old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No, very little, only just - play them or nurse them you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 But you didn't bathe them or change their nappies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh no, no. I used to make a lot of their }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 toys}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 , I was very very a handy at making things, I used to make a lot of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 oys. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How much of your earnings would you give to your wife at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Well I suppose seventy-five percent, eighty percent - I had very little myself, I knew that - we'd got to mai
ntain this home to the best of our ability so it was up to me to forgo all me pleasures that I might have got with a bit of extra pocket money so I had to forgo that altogher. I had to put up with whatever few bob that - was going, was spare really, that 
she could spare.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
You moved about five times but the flat you had longest had three rooms, were there any relatives or lodgers living with you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you have any paid help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Was the washing done at home or sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Always done at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 The wife couldn't take it along to the laundry and get it done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh no. Nothing like that. Oh no, they'd got their own - oh no, that - that was unheard of, taking your own laundry to a laundry, good Lord, unless you paid their own price of course, which was most exorbitant - beyond our means.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did your wife make any clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh yes. She did when the - when they were young - youngsters you see, from - from when they were born to about a twelve month you see. Oh yes, she used to make their little vests and pinafores and frocks and one thing and another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 And did she mend your clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 And mend - oh yes, did what mending she could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Were your clothes new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well as I told you, s
ometimes we'd - I'd be paying off a suit and perhaps see this one hanging outside a pawnshop and - go and pay a tanner a week off that. They were secondhand - unredeemed pledges.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 You'd have no special time of the year for buying these?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh no, no. No. Just when the - needs arose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How about shoes? Were they new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Well they were generally - generally a shoemaker perhaps got some repaired - shoes repaired and they hadn't called for them. Perhaps people had moved away or they c
ouldn't afford to - pay the shoemaker's fee so they had to let 'em go. Well then he'd have a sale now and again. Perhaps put half a dozen or so pairs in his window. How much do you want for them? Oh eight bob. Got and tried 'em on. If they fitted you had 
them. Oh yes, you'd get a repaired pair of shoes for seven or eight bob, that was quite reasonable.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you help in the house with any cooking or washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Well I prepared the vegetables whenever I could and always helped with the washing up, after - after our meals. Until the eldest girl was - able to assist. Then I left it to her. That was giving her some domestic knowledge you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
How about repairs or improvements to the house, did you do anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Always did my own dec
orating. Always. And - you see, if I did me own - I'd ask the landlord, I said, look - I want this room done up. Well - all right, you do it up, tell me what it - what it cost you and I'll - I'll - I'll pay for all the - all the stuff that you have to buy
, whitewash and wallpaper and paste and paint. Oh he generally used to fork out that way but he wouldn't - he wouldn't send a man in to do the job. If they could get out of it by me doing it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 It makes it much cheaper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh of course it woul
d. And I got the colour that I wanted and the - and the articles that I wanted you see, the best wallpaper and nice - nicest paint I could get, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Did you ever have much to do with the children as they got older, did you ever tell them stores or take them out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh always took them out whenever I could. Sunday morning I always had - one of the children out with me, always. If the weather was all right of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 You'd take them out in the pram would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Take 'em out in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 the pram}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 , oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 So you took them out from all ages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you ever read aloud to them and this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well if they were old enough to understand, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How about dressing or undressing them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh yes, I - well - get s
o and so ready for bed will you Harry and - while - and well I'd do that you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did the children have any regular household tasks that they had to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
No. No, they helped when they could you see, well of course - you see the - the eldest girl, she was getting on round about ten or eleven, you see she was able to do quite a bit about the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 But she pleased herself did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
No, she took it as a duty more than - I used to say, come on Winnie, wash up, well she - she'd make her go and wash up you see, or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What time did the children go to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh round about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 eighties}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Was that a strict bedtime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Not really, not really - you know - not right up to the hour or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did the children share a bed or a bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Well when the - when the second boy was born of course we had to have a cot for him in the - in the girls bedroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
What were the sleeping arrangements for the family, you had two bedrooms did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh yes. Our own and one for the children of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Which room did you use for bathing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Generally the kitchen, or the scullery. 'Cos I told you we had the gas stove in the scullery and a - a bungalow bath or perhaps a - hip bath or something like that you know, well it was 
either the scullery or in front of the kitchen fire. If - if it - if the girls had a bath well I had to clear out of it. 'Cos she was getting along then you see. Nine or ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 When was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 bath night}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Generally on a Friday or Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 When did the children have clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Once a week. Generally put 'em clean on for Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Where were your meals eaten?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well mostly in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you ever eat in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Only if we got company, like Sunday perhaps or a - 
a birthday or something like that. Just have one or two of our aunts and uncles and then we'd go into the - what we called the parlour. The front room, the best - best room of the lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What sort of cooking equipment did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh just saucepans and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 frying}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  pans, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Was it a gas stove?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Gas stove, yes. 'Course we had a little Larbet range which - oven one side and boiler the other, I don't know whether you remember those do you? Closed in ranges, with plates on the top you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 You had one of those as well did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh yes, we had the kitchen - kitchen range you see. Little Larbert range. And a gas stove in the scullery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you use the range much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh yes, we always had that fire going. 'Cos as I say when 
we - when we were - kids, when I was at home with mother and father - before I got married - you'd generally got a pot of stew or something going on there, soup - pea soup or something like that, always got this pot of - stock you might call it - on top o
f the stove. So that we always - if we want something - well a cup of - a cup of soup or something like that of a night time before we went to bed it was always there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What time did you eat breakfast, when you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 According to what time
 I'd got to go to work, sometimes my jobs six o'clock in the morning when I'm back at Price's. Well we come home to breakfast then. We get three quarters of an hour for breakfast time. It used to be half past - eight o'clock until a quarter to nine, that 
was our breakfast time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 And you just lived across the road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh yes, it wasn't far, I could go home for breakfast you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you used to have breakfast with the children?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh they - sometimes, yes, they hadn't gone to school you see and }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 - well they had to eat where get}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
 - corner of the table along with em the other side,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What did you normally have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh - more often than not it was a rasher - and - rasher of bacon and an egg. Or a boiled egg.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What did the children used to have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Mostly bread and jam, we couldn't afford much else for 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Was Sunday breakfast any different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh yes, we generally used to get a bit - bit of a luxury on Sunday - mornings. Might be a tin of sardines on toast or something like that, very frugal but - there was always something different on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What did you do for a midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh it was always a roast, roast and a - a pudding you know always. And if we had a dinner - just - just according to what the 
sweet was, it could have been a suet pudding you see with jam or Yorkshire pudding and jam, if we couldn't turn our plate upside down, we'd cleared our plate, if we couldn't turn our plate upside down we got no sweet. Back }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 in our}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  kid -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 I'm talking about your married home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh married, oh well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What did you do for midday meals there, did you used to go home from Price's?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh yes. When I was working at Price's I did. Of course if I was working further }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 a field}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  I used to get a bob for me fare and me dinner money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Did the children come home to midday meal as well or did they have that at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Well now you're talking about before I got married or - well there was only the girl and the little boy you see. Well if - invariable they had something - a canteen at their school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 So there'd just be you and your wife home for dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Me and my wife that's right. That's so.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What sort of things did you have then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh meat pudding or a chop, piece of steak, you'd get a b
it of steak for about sixpence you know or fourpence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How about the evening meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh perhaps a pair of kippers or - smoked haddock. Bloater or fresh herring, soused herring or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Were Sunday meals any different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well
 generally a - something a bit extra on Sundays you see we - perhaps we'd have some - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 shrimps}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  and winkles for tea or something like that you know. Just a little something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Your wife didn't make any bread or jam or that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No, no. No, just plain cooking, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you have any tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No, they were - almost unheard of in my younger days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How many times a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 week}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 You talking about before - in my married life? Well I
'd got a - a midday meal every day, either at home or - when - if - wherever I was working - out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 So you had meat every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Yes, you could always get a - a cut from the joint and two vegetables for sixpence. Or perhaps it'd be a - a meat pudding, or meat pie, potatoes and greens and a - a penny pudding afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you have tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
No. Well there was hardly any - there was only corned beef about - in those days, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did your wife ever have to short so that you or the children could have more?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No I don't think so, we shared what we'd got you know, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Were you on heavy work, did you have to have extra?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
No, didn't have to - if it was there we had it but if it - well when I was on that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 tram road}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  you see with a - digging - digging out these granitecess or wheelbarrow full of - full of granitecess up to where they were required. Buckets of water and so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
In some cases the woman has to go without a bit in order that the man can have enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Yes. That's so, yes. Well that's generally the vogue that was in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Were the children allowed to talk during meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh yes, if - if there was - if the necessity arose, but we - we didn't stop them talking if they wanted to. Unless they were neglecting their food - here, get on with your meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did they have to eat everything that was cooked or could they choose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No choice, we - we only had the one things, either that or go without.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you make them eat everything or could they leave some of their food?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Well they - if they didn't want it they left it, that's - that was that. They got nothing in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 lieu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  of. That's right, they had what was going or if they - if they didn't want it well they went without.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did th
ey have to wait until things on the table were offered to them or could they ask for them, the salt and things like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Well, no, if - if - if it was ready and they sat down well - the meal would be served up to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Could they bring toys or books to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Not while the meal was in progress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did they have to hold their knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh yes. Mother was very particular about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 When did members of the family leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh when they'd f
inished. Or - if they were young enough you - they'd ask, can I leave the table mum? Oh yes. They couldn't, you know, push their plate back and get up and walk out, they wouldn't - wouldn't allow them to do that. Oh no, we - tried to teach 'em table manne
rs.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Did all the family present sit down at the table at the same time for the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Very seldom, there wasn't room enough for one thing you see, so - if when the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 meal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  was ready and the - and the kids were available, well, come on - here'd your d
inner, now sit down and have it. There wasn't room enough for us all to sit down and it wasn't convenient all at one time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 You only had two children didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 You only had a small kitchen did you with just a small table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh yes
, just a small - well something like this. Sometimes smaller that this wherever we were living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you have regular places at the table or did you just sit anywhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Sit anywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Who served the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Mother as a rule.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Were you served in a certain order?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh no. No. If was - if the kids were ready and - and the meal was ready well mother served it up to 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How about when the children were too young to feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 My own children you're speaking of now, yes?
 Oh no, the girl was, as I tell you, the girls was about - ten when the second one was born.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How old were the babies when they joined the family meals at the table?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Well we generally - if the - if it was a baby we'd generally got a high chair with a little table in front you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 And had them up to the table in that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
When your children were young did you feel there was a right and a wrong way to bring up children?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh yes - certainly. When they were old enough they wen
t to Sunday school, we saw that they went. And they went to church Sunday after - went to Sunday school in the afternoon and if the weather was all right we'd let them go Sunday morning to - to the service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you and your wife have the same ideas about bringing up children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
I think so, we didn't very often disagree at the way things were happening at home, we never hardly disagreed. If she said a thing I wouldn't cross her, you see, oh no, that's not the way, I - no, whatever she said went. Unl
ess it was something very flagrant - flagrant of course. We agreed, that's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Was there anyone you used to talk to if you were worried about the children?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well I didn't, perhaps the wife did, I wouldn't know about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Was your mother alive when the children were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Yes, mother was very very ill - before - and the time was coming along - and my sister who lived next door to where I was living when I first got married - her; confinement was due about the same time as my ow
n was, and - and mother - she said, I'm not going to die before I saw you - see you two girls out of your jobs. And she didn't. But - when she was dying - now wait a minute, let me get this right. Oh when she died the girls had both had - my wife and my s
i
ster both got their children, had both had their confinements rather, mother had died in the meantime and they weren't - they was just about a few days after the children were born. So they - they - or father, he allowed the cortege to - be driven past ou
r houses, as I say, we lived next door to one another and the two - two girls were propped up in the window and watched mother's funeral go by. Very tragic, but there - there it was. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Can you tell me some of the things you felt that you ought to do
 for your children, what sort of things you thought were important, things like affection, safety, food, discipline, no important do you think these sort of things were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Well table manners for one thing and - cleanliness for another. Shoe shine for another thing you see, oh - we - you know, we brought them up as they should - as we thought they should have been brought up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you want them to share their worries with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well - we had to, if they'd got something to recount, we had to - we
 had to listen to their tale of woe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How did you want them to behave towards you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Well in - differential sort of - of away, you know, they'd got to be respect - we've got to be respected.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 When the children were young did you ever both mana
ge to leave them so you could go out together in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Well, now and again you see, perhaps mother - if mother had a - a strenuous week, come on, I'll take you up the pictures tonight, and the girl was old enough to look after the - her young 
baby brother so - we were - used - used to go about six and we were home about nine so wasn't too long you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How did you get on when your eldest daughter was still young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well we used to - if we went to the pictures and - before the second on
e was born we used to take her with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 When she was quite a babe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh yes. I used to like to give mother a weekly treat you see, going to the pictures it was only about threepence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you let your children join in when grown ups were talking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Well - unless sit was something, you know, they shouldn't have said - we didn't take much notice of it. On the whole, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What did you bring them up to consider important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Cleanliness, honesty - and truthfulness. Yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you tell them they should hit back or not when another child hurt them?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh yes, you - if they come in crying, oh so and so hit me. Go and pay him back again, go on, yes. Make them stick up for themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Were there any other children you discouraged them from playing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No, we never barred them, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 If your children did something you disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well perhaps they'd get a slap and sent up to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you both do this, either of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh mother generally inflicted the punishment, I never - I never raised my hand to the children, oh no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Do you remember any particular occasion when you had to punish them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No. No, they were - as children they were very very well behaved. I 
say it as shouldn't perhaps. They - we saw that they behaved themselves always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 So this punishment didn't happen very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No, very very seldom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Would you say that your children received the ideas that they had about how to behave from both of you or did one of you play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No, I think we were both amenable to whatever was happening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Who looked after the children while your wife was at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well the girls at school you see, and then - wel
l of course when the - when the baby was born - she had to - put it in a pram and take it over to Chelsea, to start her work at eight and then her sister used to look after the baby by while the - while the wife was at work. Mind you it wanted a bit of do
ing you know to get over there. Oh yes, walk from Battersea to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Chelsea{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 with a pram. With a kid in it, and I used to go over of a night you know and - perhaps push the pram home. Eight in the morning to eight o'clock at night that was the working hours in the laundry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How did you feel about leaving the children with someone else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
We had to put up with it. Yes, and - and hoped that we got the best we could for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Some people think that children should be with the mother all the time and others think it's not necessary and it does them good to see other people quite a lot, what did you think at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
I thought the same thing. They don't want to be tied to their mother's apron strings all their life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 When your children had a birthday would it be different from any other day?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Well, perhaps we'd have let the - let her invite one or two of her little friends in, get a bit of a spread for them you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did they have any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well what we could afford you see, it was very very small whatever it was.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What did you and your wife do with the children on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh - oh we - oh I suppose - we'd either have a - a - aitch bone of beef or a - or a chicken or something like that, you now, something out o
f the ordinary roast meat, and - we used to all hang our stockings up of a night time you know, we generally got apple, orange, a bright new penny, a few sweets and a penny toy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 I'm talking about your children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh, my own children. Oh well, we d
id the best we could you see, well - if - if we got anything that we could spare she - we'd let - let the girl fetch a couple of her friends in to tea or something like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 So she'd bring friends in on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you have any musical instruments in your married home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Yes, I - paid half a crown a week a for a piano. A pound down and a - half a crown a week until the - piano was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 apair}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  for. Generally ran out about twenty pounds altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Was this before the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you ever make music together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Musical evenings you mean? Oh yes, sometimes, we had friends round Sunday evening you know, I'd play the piano and - perhaps the girl'd sing, mother'd sing, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Usually when friends came in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Friends or - friends or relatives, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What sort of games did you play with the children? Or your wife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Well I can't say any games, we didn't have games or nothing, just romp with them that's all. Yes, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you have any books in your married home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Yes, I had quite a few books. I was very fond of reading, and I still am. And - I - used to belong to the library, and when I was at Price's we had a - a library of our own there, had 
about fifteen hundred books there and - oh - Three Muskateers you know and The Lady in White and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 You liked to get adventure yarns?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you have any magazines in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Father - oh yes, we used - I used to have some peri
odicals, Tit-Bits, Answers was another - periodical we got, Strand magazine was another one. Oh yes, and - then there was the girls and boys books, the Girls Friend and the Boys Best Friend and usual comics you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How about newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well I
 always used to have what was then known as Lloyds News, it's now the People. Always had that on Sunday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you get books from anywhere else except the library?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well if - if perhaps a - a junk shop you know, they'd have - some old paper
backs o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 r something you know, tuppence - t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
eepence, a penny each some of 'em. Oh yes, I'd buy - buy them if I thought I liked the title.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you ever read aloud to your wife or the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh no. No, once I got my nose stuck in a book I wanted some shifting.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Were the children taken out visiting neighbours or relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh if - yes, I used to take them }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 over}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
 to see my old grandmother - my own children you mean? Oh I'd take them to see my - their aunts you see or cousins or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 It was usually you who took them was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Were they taken out shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Well if they were too young to be left at home you see, oh yes, mother used to put them in a pram you see and - take 'em with her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What did you go on Bank Holidays?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Well - if we could afford it - now we could go from Clapham Junction or the Crystal Palace for one and six return, admission to the Palace as well, you see, and stop there all day long perhaps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 So if you were in funds you'd go out for the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Or else perhaps they'd have a fair on Clapham Common or Wimbledon Common, somewhere like that you see, and we'd take the kids to the fairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you ever manage to go away for a holiday before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No, a weekend at 
Littlehampton was the first holiday that I had away from home. A weekend, the wife and I and the kiddie. Saved up religiously for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What year was this, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Was before the war. Yes. about '15 or '16 I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you go regularly after that, did you manage every year after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh yes, yes. Were then in what we called a thrift club at work, we used to put sixpence or a shilling a week away in that. And if I was doing all right you see, well then that accumulated up, that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Where did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Well - somewhere along the south coast, sometimes it was Clacton, but more often it was Eastbourne or {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Brighton{\*\xmlclose}, Southend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Why did you choose these places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Not - no particular reason. Perhaps we'd have a - have 
a chat with mum, where would you like to go for a holiday this year? Oh I think I'd like to go somewhere - so and so. Oh all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you all go, your wife and children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh yes. Oh we didn't leave the kids at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What sort of activities on holiday did you have at these places before 1918?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Well - I was very athletic. I was a wonderful swimmer, I'm saying it myself, I was a wonderful swimmer. Ad - I could play football and cricket in their seasons you know, and also belonged to the i
nstitute at work and we used to go out playing other clubs at other firms, indoor games you know in the winter or with - a contest for cricket and football in the summer. That was - that was my activities.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Could you tell me how you spent Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
When I was married? Generally used to go over to Chelsea. To football. Oh I was - do you know, I've been all over the country watching Chelsea because they used to run - these cheap half day excursions see on the rail - perhaps half a cr
own, three bob, Swindon - Watford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Was this before the first world war they used to do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh yes. Oh yes. Now on Sundays - there was a - a firm called the National Sunday League, and - you could go down to Brighton for - three bob before half
 past nine, after half past nine it was half a crown for a day return to Brighton. Well they used to run these National Sunday League - now - another one they had, you - you left midnight - train from Liverpool Street to Yarmouth for five bob. Five bob yo
u know. Used to - seven to - seven to midnight and you down there about four or five o'clock in the morning and you'd got to leave there about four or five o'clock in the afternoon to get home by eleven o'clock at night. About a six hour run you now.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 W
hat else did you do on Sundays at this time, did you always have special clothes for yourself and the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh yes, generally had a best Sunday suit on, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you think it wrong to work or enjoy yourself on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh no. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you allow the children to play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Well well - let run out - out in the streets you know, they'd play games with other kids; until it was time for Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you attend a place of worship or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 I didn't, myself, neither did the wife.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Was grace said at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Very seldom. According to whether we had a certain - certain relative there that was religiously inclined. And then, you know, just a bit of a show off, common, sit down, we'll say grace now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 But your children used to go to the Sunday school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Were the children taught to say prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Yes. We were - they were all told to say their prayers when we went them up to bed. Yes. Whether they did or not we don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Before 1918 did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you or your wife vote before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh yes, the females got their - females had got their vote previous to that hadn't they, oh yes, we always voted. We always voted, yes, and it was always Labour. Father voted Labour so we - I took it and the wife took what I thought.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Could you tell me why you held these Labour views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Not particularly. I know they were for the work
ing classes. Although the Labour were for the working classes but the - Conservatives, or Tories as we know 'em now they were - they were the up and - oh yes. they were for better off people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you or your wife ever feel under any pressure from anyb
ody to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 Did you ever do any sort}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  for the parties at election times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Your only activity was to vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Only, yes, that's right, just recorded our votes and that was that. I sometimes would go to a political meeting and hear their views - the Town Hall you see or - the baths or wherever they were holding these meetings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 When you and your wife were not working how did you spend your time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well we used to get - be visited by my sister 
and her husband, we used to play cards and about once a fortnight we go to their place, generally on a Sunday evening, and - the next fortnight they'd come to us. We had tea you know and then - game of cards, perhaps me and the chap'd go out and have a dr
ink, take back a - a bottle of beer and we'd have a drink and perhaps a card session 'til about eleven o'clock at night. Then - they'd go home to their place or we'd come home to our place, whichever place we were in.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Was this mainly with relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh yes, my own sister and her husband.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Did you have any neighbours you used to do this sort of thing with or did you keep to the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
No, I used to go to whist drives quite a lot, about three a week - if I was not - otherwise engaged I d
id a lot of swimming in my young day and I was a very good swimmer I don't mind saying, and we had a competition for the - factories south of the Wash and - the North of the Wash they had the same, certain - perhaps half a dozen factories you know, and - 
w
e had - made up teams and the champions of the south had to go and play the champions of the north. Well this - this was held at Port Sunlight, it was sponsored by Lord Leverhulme. And - anyway our team of four, we won the - I was one of the four in the t
e
am you see - we won the south so we had to go up there - it was all the - oil and candle industries, that's where it was, that - that sort of factory you see that were involved in that - that group of - kind of manufactures. So - anyway we went up there, 
which necessitated me getting up about - five o'clock in the morning, getting myself ready, and got to go to Kings Cross to catch this train. We left there about - seven or eight o'clock I suppose and we got up to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
Liverpool{\*\xmlclose}. When we got up to Liverpool - we had to have some lunch, we went under the Mersey Tunnel to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Birkenhead{\*\xmlclose}
, to our - to Lord Leverhulme, Port Sunlight, that's where we went. When we got there - which we'd never had before was a circular path and we had to swim in strings you know, we got - s
trings that we'd got to keep in that channel all the time. Well - we had this competition, our - our team of four played the champion team of - it had - on the programme it had Mr so and so, so and so, and so and so and so and so, A.N. Other. I don't like
 the look of that, well anyway, we had to go through with it. We just got beaten by a few seconds, nothing in it, we could have won, but - later on in the programme and exhibition swim by Mr so and so, the - champion breast stroke swimmer of 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Cheshire{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. I said, that's Mr A.N. Other who was swimming for the Port Sunlight team. What a carve up though day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Do you remember what year this was roughly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh I've got the - I've got the gen in there somewhere. I could tell you if I - if you was interested that far, I'll get it out. I've got the programme somewhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did your wife ever go to the whist drives with you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Very - very very seldom. She hadn't enough confidence. But in her own little circle we'd - she did play, but she hadn't got enough con
fidence to go to whist drives, she went to - come to one or two and anyway - she dropped a brick there, we were playing against a couple there and - she says, you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 elder}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  a players suit. He said, well what of it, I can do - I can play cards as I like madam. 
She said, well I don't like rebuffs so - she wouldn't go anymore. Which he did - he did play - well it - it's permissible but it's up to you to beat that sort of play you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did she go anywhere else in the evening with you or did she prefer to stay 
at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well - if we had a - when we had our annual swimming }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 gala}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
 or we had our sports meetings she would come there, and on a Saturday afternoon - I was playing football, if I wasn't playing I always - always used to go and see the team and she'd c
ome along with me, plus - plus my little daughter, she always came as well. We'd got our own sports ground you see, down Earlsfield. Oh yes, we were always a united family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
What time did you get home from work in the evening while you were at Price's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh - oh yes, I was home in about - less that ten minutes, I used to come home for breakfast when we started at six in the morning and went - had a breakfast time. We had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 three quarters}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  of an hour for breakfast and I was able to come home then and ha
ve me breakfast and get back to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What time did you get home in the evening before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Well we finished up at half past five. And I was home at a quarter to six easily. Unless we were working overtime of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did either of you go to any clubs, institutes or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Only our own - factory institute. But then - we used to - in the wintertime - we were invited out to other institutes - local factories you know, we used to play - crib, dominoes, whist, billiards, you know, dominoes 
and cards, darts, chess. Oh yes, we - that was - out and home games you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 You mentioned the National Sunday League?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you still belong to this then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 There was no membership. Not at I know of. But they used to advertise these
 cheap trips, now you go to Brighton for half a crown, after half past ten, if you wanted to go before half past - say from eight o'clock - six o'clock in the morning Sunday mornings, you could go for three and six or three bob I think it was.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 So as far as you know they just organised cheap travel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
That's right, it was just a - well I don't know what they - what the institute was of this National Sunday League, what it was - what it was formed for I do not know but anyway, they used to advertise
 these cheap railway trips you know, and every Sunday - day trips to somewhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 That's all you know about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 That's all, I don't know what they're other activities were I'm sure.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 When you were first married did you belong to any sick clu
bs or funeral clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh yes. Yes, when I - when I - been to - when I'd worked in the factory - when you were eighteen you had a three years probation and they - and the foreman had to report on your - conduct, your work and your timekeeping, and if t
hose three years, three separate reports on your behaviour, son on and so on, if they were favourable you were allowed to join what they called their pension fund, which was non-}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 contributory}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  but - if when you were - if you were - incapacitated and couldn't
 work any further and you'd done twenty years there they would pension you off at ten shillings a week. But otherwise you had to wait until you were sixty. And then you still got the ten bob a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Before 1914 that was quite generous?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh yes, oh it was a nice gesture you know, of yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 thrift}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  clubs or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Yes, well - they had a thrift - what they call a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 thrift}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
 and loan club. Well we used to pay a bob a week for that for our holiday you see, put that by. And i
f you were financially embarrassed or wanted a loan you could go and borrow it at sixpence in the pound interest, that's all it was, and that money was all shared out in July when they cut - closed the factory for a fortnight you see, fortnights holiday, 
everybody except - maintenance people had a fortnights holiday with pay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Was this before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Yes. Yes. Very good, yes, it was good. Yes. That was a lovely firm to work for. You couldn't work for a - a better firm, even - well even now - if you got a job at Price's you were there for life - provided you behaved yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you ever go to racing at all or did you bet?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No. No, I - never a gambler.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How about theatres and concerts and music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well - I used to do a lot of
 entertaining myself. See, well if - if anybody was out of work for a long time, had a long illness, the public house - if - if - well mostly - most of the chaps had got their own local you see, well if he was a - if he was a - habitual of the local the l
a
ndlord would say, going to have a smoling concert for old Bill Snith or Bloggs or whatever his name was. Well we had - those who could would go up and give a turn. And - it would - you know, just - they'd buy their beer and have their smokes you see and t
hese turns you know, it made a nice evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
How did they actually raise the money, did they pass a hat round or was there an entrance fee or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Yes - well we used to charge 'em about fourpence or sixpence admission. And then we'd have a whip 
round you see, while - while the show was going on. And it was generally of a Saturday night when - every - every workman had - had had his pay and perhaps got a few bob to spend so that was - that was the - appropriate night to have it. Oh yes, and then 
it was all handed to him you know. Or his widow, if he died or - anything like that you know. Any - any deserving case that's what they used to do, a smoling concert they called it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 So a good public house was quite an asset in the neighbourhood then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh yes, well they nearly always had a big room over the - over the whole of the - which was what they called a club room. And then these pubs, they used to hold what they called slate clubs. Did you know about those? Well they're sick - kind of sick c
lub, you paid a tanner a week you know and - if you was laid up you got perhaps eight or ten bob a week while you were laid up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you still keep these up while you were in Price's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh yes. Oh yes. And also they had a sick club - in Price's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
How about cinemas, did you or your wife go to cinemas before the first world war very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh yes. Yes, we always went once a week. Well it was only about threepence to go in at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you have time left after all this for any hobbie
s, did you collect anything or keep any pets?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Well I used to make the childrens toys you know, I made a lot of toys, I was very constructive.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Were these wooden toys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Wooden toys mainly, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you ever have a garden, did you do any gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No. Very very little. Well we - we were mostly sub-}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11361879\charrsid15100875 tenants}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
 you see, and the people we were tenants of, they - it was their garden so I never had a chance. I was never much interested in garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did your wife ever go out on her own wi
thout you, did she have any interests which you didn't share?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 I can't recall any. No, we were just - we lived for one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did anyone outside the home help your wife to look after the house or family?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did your wife have any friends of her own, apart from hour relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Relatives - no. No, it was she and I for - all our lives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 You said that friends weren't invited into your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
No, not out of the way you know, not - we didn't make any special occasions of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you ever visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
No, I can't say that I did, not any special friends. Unless we were invited you know, perhaps - they knew the wife and I were interested in card playing, we're going to - would you like to come and make
 a foursome one evening? Yes, that's - we'd go round, well that was about all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Did you make any of your own amusements apart from card games, did you have musical evenings when your relatives came round or was it mainly out at the concerts that you did this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh no, if they come round and they - wanted to go - we'd light the fire in what we called the parlour, the front room you know, and - perhaps we'd sit down there and have a - my sister used to sing a lot to her - to her old - we
ll not old peoples club but I don't know she used to go out singing I know but she was invited the same as I was. And then I had a young - brother, he was - he was - doing extra turns on music halls. Oh we were a musical family, apart from the fact that m
y father was, as I told you, a lovely musician but he had no time to teach any of us children. Had no time for it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 But it seems to have come out in several of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh yes, yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Your home was rented before the first world war, 
did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Did what? Well it was generally - we paid our rent to the people who we took the rooms off you see in the house. Oh yes, it was sub-let to us you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How did you feel about them as landlords?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well - 
fairly well you know. Oh yes, pretty fair. They were a bit hard hearted if you wanted your place done up you know, if you like to do the job they'd pay for the stuff kind of thing and that was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 So it wasn't too bad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh no, it wasn't too bad, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
During your early married life, up until 1918, did you have to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Very often - very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What did you think about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Well, we just tolerate, we - there was nothing you could do about it, nothing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Would you say on the whole you were better off in your married life than you were before you were married or not, how would you say your married life compared with your childhood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Well I was - I was poor when we got married, of course I was onl
y - a frugal wage you see, never earned more than a pound or a guinea a week, never. Now when I went to Price's - I was earning about twenty-four bob a week which was about sixty hours. It was all piecework, packing case making, and it was a most cut }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14182191\charrsid15100875 throat}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
 job. Well for instance - I was - as I told you, in the summer time when they couldn't mould the candles we were on short time, that's what fed me up with - working at Price's. Well I went over to a case making firm over at Fulham - told 'em who I was, yo
u know. Oh yes, he said, yes, I can give you a job. I said, well what are you paying? How much do you think they offered? Threepence and five eights of a penny an hour. Threepence and five }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14182191\charrsid15100875 edighths}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  - they went down even that - talk about skinning a toad, t
hree and threepence and five eighths. I said, make it fourpence I'll come and work here. No, threepence and five edighths is our rate. Unless you're exceptional - exceptionally - a good as a casemaker. I'll tell you another incident. When I was out of wor
k we'd got - we'd got to walk all over the place, well I'd been right over London, somewhere up the East End, coming back I came - coming }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14182191\charrsid15100875 over}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  Southwark Bridge and - the others - Surry side of it they've got some arches, well underneath the bridge I suppose
, well anyway - could have been a railway arch but anyway - Smith and Stevens or some such a name as that - packing case makers to the trade. Cor never had - never knew of the existence of that, used to go to director and get all the - case making firm yo
u
 know and - go and see these people. Well I went there, he said, well - he says, unfortunately we're on strike at the moment, our chaps are on strike. He said, and I've got a couple of very important jobs, he said, I've got to get two cases for a piano, t
o
 hold a piano, each. He said, if you like to take a chance, he said, but I'm not guaranteeing anything, he says, if you like to come and take a change - could you make 'em? I said, yes, I could do any - I said, I can make toilet soap boxes, about six inch
e
s round, six inches square, I said, I can make you a piano case, and I could, I could make any sort of case. So he says, like to take the chance he says, you can come and have a go. So anyway - said, all right, I'll come in the morning. I got over there a
b
out seven o'clock in the morning I got on with this job. Got lengths of timber you know I only had to cross cut it, with a - there was no machinery going of course, the chaps were on strike, if they heard - heard the machine - saw going - they'd want to k
n
ow who was working there. Well anyway - he says, you'd better muffle your hammer the best you can. Well I didn't make a noise, anyway I did this job. For which I got the magnificent sum of half a crown each. Half a crown each you know, you just imagine th
e size of a piano case.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How long did it take you to do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh about three or four hours I suppose. And anyway I did this one and he was quite pleased with it. He said, well if, at any time, he says, you want a job - if - if and when our chaps 
come back to work come - he says, you can always have a job here. I've always got plenty of work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Was there any trade union activity in the trade at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Not for a long long while after that. And then the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 This wasn't union men on strike?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
No. No. I don't know, no they weren't - there was no unions there at that time, there were no unions. And then - they made a - sawyers and Casemakers, Sawyers and Packing Case Makers, they made a union and - and they got things moving, they abo
lished piecework for on thing - which was a great - great boon to us.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Can you remember roughly when it was the union got started in the Sawyer and Packing Case trade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh about 1930 I should say. Oh yes. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did you ever get any help from the Guardians or any parish or charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No. No, nothing whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Did it make any difference to you when you were ill, were you ever ill for any long period?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Not a long period, no. No, I was very very healthy and so was my wife. No
, I was very very healthy, I say I led an active life, I didn't drink a lot and - I went in for sports you know, I played cricket, football - swimming, and - you now, I kept myself pretty fit. I never abused myself. And I never raked about, as I say, I ha
d my little sweetheart who I married eventually and we lived for one another. We were sweethearts right 'til the end. I can - give you some anecdote very likely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 You told me your oldest brother was a cabinet maker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Cabinet maker, that's so. Right through his life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Your next sister worked in a laundry until she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
That's right. And - and she still went out work when she got married. Yes. Well she was engaged to a - a chap who was a conductor on the - trams, but - he lost so many da
ys through laziness or drink that - she didn't care whether she had him or not, but they were engaged. I don't know if the wedding day was fixed or not, but - she was invited to this party and in this - at this party there was a chappie - he'd just come h
ome from the Doer War, and - of course they couldn't spend any money out there and they were paid in golden sovereigns. He'd got this - I can see that chap now, he'd got a canvas belt on with all little purses }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14182191\charrsid15100875 sewn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  on, full of golden sovereigns. I reckon he
 just have had about a hundred or hundred and twenty pounds. Well there was nothing to spend it on you see, when he came home, he'd got a father and mother and no - nobody else, you know, they were - they were in the - the old man was in the gas works and
 the mother used to work so - they didn't want the money }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14182191\charrsid15100875 really}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
, they were pretty comfortably off, and nobody else at home. Well I suppose this - this - sight of the golden sovereigns you know, an - he was a nice chap mind you, and - anyway they got - got o
ut walking together you know and eventually she turned this other fellow up who she was engaged to, she told him she didn't want any more to do with him, he'd lost too many hours at - days off at work and he didn't care whether he worked or not and - she 
eventually married this chap. And - oh they were together - they had -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What did he do after he finished soldering?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
When they were married? Oh he was just a worker in the gas works, what his old man - his old man got him -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 In a gas works was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Yes, Fulham Gas works. Where the old - where his father worked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Was this labouring or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh yes, just a labourer, you know, oh yes. A gas worker you know, wheeling coke or - something like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 That's one brother and one sister, who came next?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 A younger brother of mine, and that was the one -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 You were next weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
I was the next one, yes. Then my - the next brother, he was the one - he joined the Territorials - and - as I say, he got - out o
n the music halls. He used to go up - at these music halls they had what they called an extra turn you know, you got about seven and six for one song, or ten bob for two. And - you know, he was well known, Jock Scott his name was, or that's what he went f
or, Jock. His name was Jack but he called himself Jock Scott and - he got quite a popular chap on the - on the music halls, especially our two local ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 He'd do this several evenings a week would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Oh well he would - he'd go there you know. G
o and see the manager, do you want an extra turn? Well you can come Friday night, we'll put you on Friday night or Saturday night you see. Or perhaps he'd go for an audition on a Monday you see, well, if they thought he was all right they'd give him a sho
w perhaps two nights a - two nights in that week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Did the management do this sort of thing to encourage the local audience, did they put local chaps on usually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
No - not necessarily so, no. But the audience they didn't care it was an extra turn if he was all right it was all right but if he wasn't - they'd sling anything at him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What was his normal occupation?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Just labouring you know. Until I got him a job at Price's. and he came - came there and worked with me quite a number of years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Would that have been semi-skilled work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Packing case making. 'Course he started as a - a boy really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 How about the next one in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
The next one was - well that - I'm sorry to say it but he was a ne'er do well. In fact he was
 - he was one of the - delinquents, what we'd call him in these days. For instance, there was - top of the street where we lived there was a secondhand furniture dealer. Well - he'd sold a table to a customer you know, and he said to my brother Fred, he s
a
id, will you take this to so and so tonight. Oh yes, Mr Prince. Got a barrow, put this table or whatever it was on this barrow, on the way there he went into another - rag shop or furniture bloke and sold it to him. Well - what with one thing and another 
y
ou know when - when father heard about it - he shut him up in to his - and father had a - what they a called an ante-room, that was a little room the top of the staircase. Well father's workroom. Father shut him in there, he said, you stop there 'til I te
ll you you can come}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14182191\charrsid15100875  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14182191\charrsid15100875 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
t. Give him a jolly good hiding - for doing such a thing you know, of course Mr Prince come down, what are you going to do about it? Oh well, anyway - well - Fred - he unlocked the window and run away. He was missing for a couple of days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Was he just a young lad at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh yes, only about eleven - twelve I suppose. Well - my brother, the next one to me who worked with me at Pri}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14182191\charrsid15100875 ce's, we were coming home from w}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 ork one night - I said, look there's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14182191\charrsid15100875 Fred}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  over there, come on J
ack, let's take him home. So me - me and my other brother got hold of this one, of course he was younger than both of us, and we took him home, The old man gave him a clouting then, I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14182191\charrsid15100875 forget}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  now what his next episode was, some - oh I no, there was a greeng
rocers shop, you know they used to - well they do now, stock up all the oranges and apples you know. Well he'd go along, pull one out the bottom, of course the blooming lot come down. So father went up to the police court, he was out of control, we couldn
'
t handle him, don't matter what the old man done, give him a jolly good hiding you know, he - he'd almost turn round and laugh at him. So - the magistrate heard some of these episodes that this kid had been up to you know, so - put him in a reformatory sc
h
ool, send him right up to Birmingham, and I got a letter from him, what I dug out the other day looking up some of my old papers, got a letter which he wrote from this convalescent home at Coleshill in Birmingham. Anyway whilst there they taught him talor
ing and to play a - euphonium, blooming great big brass trumpet as }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14182191\charrsid15100875 big as}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  himself really. Anyway when he come home, he done about couple of years there I suppose, when he came home he got a job with a tailor, and he was a very smart - you know, they taught 
him properly. And then he joined a - a little local band they got up, with Boys }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14182191\charrsid15100875 Brigade}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  or what but anyway - with this blessed old euphonium he used to practice Sunday morning and drive us nearly mad.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Did he work as a tailor all his life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No, I
 think he got a job as a - a shop assistant. He done quite a lot of tailoring you know, neighbours knew that he was a - he was a - proficient as a tailor you know, if they wanted a dress altered or - go and buy a secondhand pair of trousers or suit you kn
ow, trousers were too tong, well take them to Fred Scott, he'll alter them for you, he'll charge about a tanner or a bob you know. Augment his pocket money that way, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Those schools do teach people good trades, they're good training grounds?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Oh yes. Yes. Well they taught him properly, he was a jolly good tailor. Oh and he could press a pair of trousers like - oh - like nobody's business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Who came next, we've had three brothers and one sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Yes, well then there was - a younger brother named George came the next.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 What did he do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Well just got shop assistant you know or - oh mainly, yes, or - factory job I never know now. But he had a very tragic end that fellow. He was working at Prices. Well when they sent the buzz bom
bs over you know - well once - one Friday morning I think it was they were distilling spirit of turpentine at Prieces's were we was working, and this buzz bomb came over, went right into this vat where they was distilling this - spirit of turpentine, you 
j
ust imagine, a buzz bomb going in that. Set the factory alight. Cor. And he was one of two that got killed. That was his finish. No, well he had - well I was standing there watching and you could not possibly - it was inferno. You couldn't get - well you 
s
tood about - ten yards away you got scorched. And I knew he was in there and I couldn't do a thing. No, that was very tragic. Well that - after that there were the little babies came along you know but we hadn't much time for them, I couldn't tell you ver
y
 much about them at all. Except - oh the next one to him - was - little boy name of Bobby. Well when they got their summer - broke up for about four or five weeks in the summer you know, the school did, and he went up into Battersea Park along with some o
ther kids. Well in one part of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Battersea{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Park{\*\xmlclose} - they got the river flowed right the way through you see, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}
}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Chelsea{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} one side, Battersea the other side. Well he climbed over some railings, the top of which there was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14182191\charrsid15100875 concrete}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875  - about a foot or fourteen inches 
wide, and then a - a concrete embankment you see down there, keep the tide in you see. Well I suppose it - doing dares that's what they said he was doing, that was - you know, the kids dared one another to get over and walk along this - and all of a sudde
n he slipped and down he went. A very strong tide took him right up and they found him underneath a barge at Putney. He got killed that way you see. I can't tell you much more about any of the others, if there was - I don't know how - how many that was.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 We've had five brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 Then there was another one, he was a baby, he died in convulsions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 So that's seven boys with your self?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 
Then the sister was born. I can't remember - another couple after that - after her I think, they were only babies, what happened to 'em I don't know now. Can't remember. 'Cos I was away out of the family by that time. I was away married meself you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7894345 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 You don't know anything about the husband's occupations of the younger ones?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13057156 FS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9117970\charrsid15100875 No.
\par }}